name: Zdzislaw Beksinski Style
description:
If you like my contributions to the community, please consider Buying Me A Coffee or check out my other sites on AllMyLinks

TRAINING INFO

  • Trained on 47 images

  • Trained at 1024 resolution

RECOMMENDED SETTINGS

TXT2IMG - A weight of 1 works just fine and will yield some interesting results, but I recommend a weight of 0.4-0.7 for more flexibility while still keeping Bekinski's style.

PROMPTS - I highly recommend using prompts that already describe the style of Bekinski's work, including but not limited to: fog, structure, ominous, brown, sky, tombstones, tissue, decaying, backlit, bright, cracked, mysterious figure, crucifix, towering, silhouette, cliffs, orb, pillars, glowing, floating, massive, pathway, walls, gateway, portal, fossils, cloak, hooded, monolith, moon. Including prompts like these will give the best results. For a full list of the prompts/captions used for training, check the Lora file's metadata in your webgui.

modelVersions.name: v1.1
modelVersions.description: Same dataset but refined the captions so the prompts should work better and be more precise
